{"body": {"name": "DevHub Developer Contributor report by THOMAS for 08/12/2024 \\\\u{2013}\\\\u{a0}08/30/2024", "summary": "This proposal outlines the work completed over three weeks, addressing various needs and goals within the NEAR ecosystem. The focus was on improving the NEAR DevHub, including bug fixes, PR reviews, and enhancements to both the treasury dashboard and NEAR contracts, plus replacing pogoda\\\\\\'s indexers for those of the subquery network.", "category": "DevDAO Platform", "timeline": {"status": "REVIEW", "sponsor_requested_review": false, "reviewer_completed_attestation": false}, "supervisor": "theori.near", "description": "**Week 1: August 12 \\\\u{2013}\\\\u{a0}August 16**\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nMonday 12 Aug - 30 min\\\\n- Reviewed Megha her PR to improve the members page of the treasury dashboard [41](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-treasury-dashboard/pull/41)\\\\n\\\\nTuesday 13 Aug - 1 hour\\\\n- Fixed bug [922](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/pull/922)\\\\n\\\\nWednesday 14 Aug\\\\n- Standup 30 min\\\\n\\\\n**Total hours: 2 hours**\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**Week 2: August 19 \\\\u{2013}\\\\u{a0}August 23**\\\\n\\\\nMonday 19 Aug - 6 hours\\\\n\\\\n-  Started/Finished issue [923](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/923) & Created PR [924](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/pull/924) by adding updated instructions under DevHub Timeline Approved Stage\\\\n-  Made changes to the contract to make minimal sized links trackable for Joe [145](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-contract/pull/145)\\\\n\\\\nTuesday 20 August - 1 hours\\\\n\\\\n- Reviewed Megha\\\\\\'s PR [44](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-treasury-dashboard/pull/44)\\\\n- Joe used a \\\\u{2014} character in the blog after investigating I found that instead he should use - as a replacement. There is no trackable issue since there was no code changed.\\\\n\\\\nWednesday August 21 -  6 hours\\\\n\\\\n-  Standup\\\\n-  Finished [145](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-contract/pull/145)\\\\n-  Review Megha her PR [45](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-treasury-dashboard/pull/45)\\\\n\\\\nThursday 22 August - 1 hour\\\\n\\\\n-  Create issue for moving indexer [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n-  Start issue  [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)  Investigate moving the indexers to subquery \\\\n\\\\n\\\\nFriday 23 - 5 hours\\\\n\\\\n-  Reviewed Megha her PR [46](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-treasury-dashboard/pull/46) \\\\n-  Start issue  [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)  Investigate moving the indexers to subquery \\\\n\\\\n**Total hours: 19**\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**Week 3: August 26 \\\\u{2013}\\\\u{a0}August 30**\\\\n\\\\nAugust 26 - 4 hours\\\\n- Finished [145](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-contract/pull/145) by making changes to the PR based on Vlad his feedback.\\\\n- Worked on the subquery network price oracle example. Also other examples seem to not work as expected.  [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n\\\\nAugust 27 - 4 hours\\\\n- Reviewed Megha\\\\\\'s PR [47](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-treasury-dashboard/pull/47) on UI enhancements for the treasury dashboard.\\\\n- Created issue in the subql repository [2546](https://github.com/subquery/subql/issues/2546)\\\\n- Tried to make the default subquery example work. [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n\\\\nAugust 28 -  2 hours\\\\n- Standup\\\\n- Made changes to fix a bug on the proposal timeline when an admin would switch from [926](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/926)\\\\n- Contacted the subquery team on to get support. They told me they needed time to investigate the issue. This was their fix: [119](https://github.com/subquery/subql-near/pull/119)\\\\n\\\\nAugust 29 - 2 hours\\\\n- Called with Peter and Megha about the subquery node. [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n- Continued refactoring issue [916](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/pull/916)\\\\n\\\\nAugust 30 - 5 hours\\\\n- Worked on indexing a proposal now that the subquery near repository was updated and fixed. [928](https://github.com/NEAR-DevHub/neardevhub-bos/issues/928)\\\\n\\\\n**Total hours: 17 hours**\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n## Cost\\\\n\\\\n- Total hours: 38 hours\\\\n- Rate: $100/hour ~ \\\\u{20ac}90/h is an average rate for a medior freelance front end web3 developer in the Netherlands ranging from 35 (absolute beginner) to 150 (senior) [for example](https://zzpservicedesk.nl/uurtarief-freelance-developer/)\\\\n- Total amount: $3800 USD", "linked_proposals": [], "receiver_account": "thomasguntenaar.near", "requested_sponsor": "neardevdao.near", "proposal_body_version": "V0", "requested_sponsorship_usd_amount": "3800", "requested_sponsorship_paid_in_currency": "NEAR"}, "labels": [], "accepted_terms_and_conditions_version": 127161072}

{"data": {"blog": {"hackathon-resources-for-redacted-lsy0pp": {"": "We\\\\\\'re excited to have you build on NEAR and compete in the **[REDACTED]** hackathon.  \\\\n\\\\nBefore you begin, make sure you are registered at [Devpost](https://redacted.devpost.com/).\\\\n\\\\nAt DevHub, we are providing a list of resources to get started with NEAR technology and how to get help. \\\\n\\\\n*This is a living document and will get updated over time.*\\\\n\\\\n**Live DevRel and Community Support:**\\\\n- NEAR Dev Support Channels (Telegram): https://t.me/neardev\\\\n- DevHub Announcements: https://t.me/NEARDevHub\\\\n\\\\n## Quick links\\\\n\\\\nCompletely new to NEAR: \\\\n- https://docs.near.org/concepts/basics/protocol\\\\n- https://docs.near.org/concepts/protocol/account-model\\\\n\\\\nTutorials: \\\\n- https://docs.near.org/tutorials/welcome\\\\n- https://agorapp.dev/catalog/course?difficulty=&chains=near\\\\n\\\\nSmart Contracts:\\\\n- https://docs.near.org/build/smart-contracts/quickstart\\\\n- https://docs.near.org/build/smart-contracts/what-is\\\\n\\\\nFrontend Development:\\\\n- https://docs.near.org/build/web3-apps/quickstart\\\\n\\\\nChain Abstraction:\\\\n- https://docs.near.org/build/chain-abstraction/chain-signatures\\\\n- https://near.org/chain-abstraction\\\\n- https://linktr.ee/chainsignatures (All about Chain Signatures)\\\\n\\\\nAI:\\\\n- https://near.ai/\\\\n- [NEAR AI Cookbook](https://github.com/jbarnes850/near-ai-cookbook)\\\\n\\\\n## Intro to concepts on NEAR\\\\n\\\\n### Go multichain with **Chain Abstraction**:\\\\nIf you want your application to scale to large numbers of users, including users who aren\\\\\\'t using any other on-chain apps, consider chain abstraction. The idea behind chain abstraction is quite simple: blockchain technology should be abstracted away from the user experience. In other words, people should not realize when they are using a blockchain, let alone which blockchain they are using.\\\\n\\\\nTo help with this goal, NEAR Protocol allows users to create and recover accounts using email addresses, use the account without acquiring funds, and control accounts in other chains. All this happens in the most seamless way possible.\\\\n\\\\n[Fast Auth](https://docs.near.org/build/chain-abstraction/fastauth-sdk) is an SDK that makes logging in as simple as an email-based login to an off-chain application - no seed phrases or private keys to manage.\\\\n[Meta Transactions](https://docs.near.org/build/chain-abstraction/meta-transactions): With NEAR, developers can bundle transactions and subsidize gas fees for their users thanks to the baked-in meta-transactions\\\\n[Chain Signatures](https://docs.near.org/build/chain-abstraction/chain-signatures): A single NEAR account can control multiple other accounts on foreign chains.\\\\n\\\\nIf you\\\\\\'ve used blockchain apps and been frustrated by being limited to a single chain, or disappointed by clunky auth processes for multi-chain apps, NEAR offers a better solutions. NEAR accounts can [control multiple accounts](https://docs.near.org/build/chain-abstraction/chain-signatures) across different chains signatures make chain-agnostic projects simple, and are even more powerful in combination with other chain abstraction concepts.\\\\n\\\\n### **Smart Contracts** are more flexible than you think:\\\\nIf you want to create a small, decentralized backend service, you may want a smart contract. Smart contracts are small pieces of logic that live on the blockchain and are amazing for storing user information and acting on it. The name may sound like they\\\\\\'re meant for financial services, but smart contracts are very versatile and can support development of  tons of projects.\\\\n\\\\nIf you want to understand from scratch how smart contracts work, we have a dedicated docs section for them, which includes an [awesome quickstart](https://docs.near.org/build/smart-contracts/quickstart) tutorial to guide you on creating your first contract. \\\\n\\\\n### Stay up to date\\\\nAlong with these resources we have a newsletter (https://bit.ly/devhubnews) and do a weekly live show, DevHub Live, and WuASM (Wake Up & Ship More, which does not have a set schedule yet).\\\\n\\\\nOur entire video archive, which includes all live streams and community call replays are available on our [YouTube](https://youtube.com/@NEARDevHub).\\\\n\\\\nLastly, please also make sure to check out our socials to keep up to date on everything developer centric on NEAR.\\\\n[YouTube](https://youtube.com/@NEARDevHub)\\\\n[Twitch](https://twitch.tv/neardevhub)\\\\n[X](https://x.com/neardevhub)\\\\n[IG](https://instagram.com/neardevhub)\\\\n[TikTok](https://tiktok.com/@neardevhub)\\\\n[LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/near-devhub)\\\\n[Threads](https://www.threads.net/@neardevhub)\\\\n[Reddit](https://www.reddit.com/user/NEARDevHub)\\\\n\\\\nLast updated: Sept 3, 2024", "metadata": {"title": "Hackathon Resources for REDACTED", "author": "orangejoe.near", "status": "PUBLISH", "category": "reference", "subtitle": "Quick links to get started with your project", "updatedAt": "2024-09-03", "description": "Quick links to help get started with your hackathon project.", "publishedAt": "2024-08-06"}}}}, "handle": "developer-dao"}
